<h1 class="orange" style="margin-bottom:0px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a1');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">What are SUN-GARD window films?</h4>
<p id ="a1" class="hidden">SUN-GARD window films are a family of products that are applied to glass either for automotive or architectural purposes. Made from the highest grade polyester, our films are treated with various coating and laminating techniques to produce the desired color and performance characteristics. With a wide range to choose from, you are sure to find the perfect film to help control the sun's heat, UV rays and glare in your vehicle, home or office.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a2');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">How do SUN-GARD window films work?</h4>
<p id ="a2" class="hidden">By increasing the amount of solar heat that is reflected or absorbed by the film, SUN-GARD products reduce the amount of heat that is transmitted through the glass. Reducing solar heat offers a more comfortable interior space in a building or vehicle. Utilizing various processes in the construction of our films, allows us to provide a varying degree to which our films reduce solar heat transmission. Some films contain a layer of metal that provides a high amount of solar heat reflection (even though the film itself is not necessarily reflective). Other films contain no metal but still offer a level of heat rejection that will provide significant benefits. Please consult your SUN-GARD professional retailer to find out which film is best for you.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a3');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">How is SUN-GARD window film applied?</h4>
<p id ="a3" class="hidden">SUN-GARD window film is professionally installed by a well-trained SUN-GARD dealer. Most of our films are designed to be installed on the inside of your windows or glass doors. 
<br /><br />
For architectural applications: The first step is preparation which includes thoroughly cleaning the windows and the immediate surrounding work space&mdash;this could require moving furniture, removing window treatments and protecting the flooring below. Then the film is sprayed with a mounting solution to allow it to be properly positioned on the glass. Using professional tools and techniques, the installing dealer will form the film to the glass surface being sure to remove any excess water. They will then trim the edges of the film for a perfect fit and complete the process with a final squeegee technique to ensure the film is in place.
<br /><br />
For automotive applications: The glass is first thoroughly cleaned. The installing dealer will then wet the film and apply it to the outside of the window. Using a heat gun, they will form the film to the exact curvature of the window. After this, the film is carefully removed from the outside of the window and applied with a squeegee to the inside of the glass. The installing dealer will trim any excess film and will complete the installation by making sure the film is firmly in place.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a4');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Which SUN-GARD automotive window film is right for me?</h4>
<p id ="a4" class="hidden">To select the best SUN-GARD film for your vehicle, you should consult your local SUN-GARD dealer. We offer a wide range of products from an all-metal film to a metal-free, GPS friendly film. Color and performance characteristics vary from film to film. Your SUN-GARD dealer can show you swatches of each film and talk to you about the performance benefits that best meet your needs. To find a SUN-GARD dealer near you, call 888-887-2022 to speak to one of our seven service centers in the U.S. For international requests, please contact our authorized distributor for your country which can be found <a href="http://www.sungarddealer.com/where-to-buy" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a5');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Which SUN-GARD architectural window film is right for me?</h4>
<p id ="a5" class="hidden">To select the best SUN-GARD film for your home or commercial property, you should consult your local SUN-GARD dealer. We offer a wide range of products that come in various shades, colors, and offer different performance characteristics. Your SUN-GARD dealer can show you swatches of each film and talk to you about the performance benefits that best meet your needs. To find a SUN-GARD dealer near you, call 888-887-2022 to speak to one of our seven service centers in the U.S. For international requests, contact our authorized distributor for your country which can be found <a href="http://www.sungarddealer.com/where-to-buy" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a6');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Do SUN-GARD window films offer any security benefits?</h4>
<p id ="a6" class="hidden">Yes, SUN-GARD window films offer some basic security benefits including helping to hold broken glass in its frame. Our safety and security films offer enhanced levels of protection against severe weather, criminal activity, and accidents that result in glass related injuries. SUN-GARD safety and security films are made from either clear or tinted polyester that is thicker than traditional solar control film. If you are interested in enhancing the level of protection for your property, contact your local SUN-GARD dealer for more information. To find a SUN-GARD dealer near you, call 888-887-2022 to speak to one of our seven service centers in the U.S. For international requests, contact our authorized distributor for your country which can be found <a href="http://www.sungarddealer.com/where-to-buy" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a7');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">How do I maintain window film after it is installed?</h4>
<p id ="a7" class="hidden">Wait 30 days and then simply clean windows as you normally would, using standard window cleaning solution and soft, lint-free cloth. Avoid using abrasive materials that may scratch or damage the film.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('a8');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Can I install SUN-GARD film myself on my home or business property?</h4>
<p id ="a8" class="hidden">A trained installer will need to professionally fit window film to the inside of your existing windows. Professional installation will help ensure your satisfaction and provide you with the warranty protection you deserve.</p>

