<h1 class="orange" style="margin-bottom:0px;"> &nbsp; </h1>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b1');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">How long does it take for SUN-GARD window film to dry?</h4>
<p id ="b1" class="hidden">Depending on weather conditions and the film type, it can take up to 30 sometimes even 45 days for the film to fully dry and cure. During this time, you may notice small water bubbles and/or a hazy appearance. This is normal and will disappear as the film dries. Once completely dry, your SUN-GARD window film will be virtually undetectable and will look great for years to come.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b2');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">How long will SUN-GARD window film last?</h4>
<p id ="b2" class="hidden">Made with only the highest grade raw materials, SUN-GARD window films are made to last for many years. The exact life of the film depends on the film type, the climate and the type of glass in which it is installed. Most automotive applications last in upwards of 10 years. Architectural films can easily last 10 to 15 years, sometimes longer. The important thing to remember is that all of our films are backed by a manufacturer's warranty. Speak with your SUN-GARD dealer for warranty details as some restrictions may apply.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b3');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Will SUN-GARD film kill my house plants?</h4>
<p id ="b3" class="hidden">No, SUN-GARD window film will not harm your house plants or anything else on the interior of your home. As a matter of fact, SUN-GARD film will help protect your flooring and furnishings from fading caused by exposure to UV rays and solar heat.
</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b4');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Will SUN-GARD window film cause glass to break?</h4>
<p id ="b4" class="hidden">While adding solar control film to glass will increase the glass temperature, properly chosen film will not cause glass to break. There are a number of factors that can contribute to the rare case of glass breakage. These include the amount of external shading, interior shading, glass size and shape, age of the glass, previous glass breakage history, certain film types on certain types of glass, interior versus exterior temperatures, and more. With more than 35 years of experience, we are able to make proper film-to-glass recommendations thus minimizing the risk of glass breakage. We also offer limited warranty protection against glass breakage and seal failure for properly applied installations. Consult your SUN-GARD dealer for details and to obtain a copy of our architectural film warranty.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b5');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">How much UV protection will SUN-GARD film provide?</h4>
<p id ="b5" class="hidden">All SUN-GARD automotive and architectural window films can block up to 99% of harmful ultraviolet rays. This can help protect against skin-related issues including skin cancer. UV rays also contribute to fading of interior furnishings and flooring. SUN-GARD helps reduce fading by not only blocking UV rays but also blocking up to 80% of harmful solar heat.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b6');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">What energy savings can I expect from installing solar control film?</h4>
<p id ="b6" class="hidden">Installing SUN-GARD solar control film reduces the amount of solar heat entering your home or property which can result in lower cooling costs in the summer. However, determining exact energy savings can be difficult because many factors contribute to energy use such as the fluctuating cost of fuel, amount of direct sun exposure, type of film installed, type of glass, and many others. However, typical payback in energy savings is usually 2-5 years, sometimes less. Speak with your local SUN-GARD dealer regarding your particular situation; they can help you analyze and determine potential savings.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b7');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Where can I buy SUN-GARD window film?</h4>
<p id ="b7" class="hidden">Our films are sold through a large network of independent dealers worldwide. In the U.S., you can find a dealer in your area by calling one of our seven service centers at 1-888-887-2022. They will direct you to the closest film dealer. Outside of the U.S., contact our authorized distributor for your country which can be found <a href="http://www.sungarddealer.com/where-to-buy" target="_blank">here</a>.</p>

<h4 onclick="toggle_visibility('b8');" class="textbutton" onmouseover="this.style.textDecoration='underline'" onmouseout="this.style.textDecoration='none'">Are SUN-GARD window films manufactured in the U.S.?</h4>
<p id ="b8" class="hidden">Yes, all SUN-GARD solar control films are manufactured in our production facility located in St. Petersburg, Florida. We distribute our products through a network of independent distributors to more than 70 countries. We also own seven distribution centers in the United States. With such an expansive supply channel, we can provide our quality products to you in an efficient and cost-effective manner.</p>

